[
  "Ian Wood transformed a family-owned fishing business based in Aberdeen, Scotland into Wood Group, a multinational oil services company. ",
  "He joined the firm in 1962, became CEO in 1967, and took the business public in 2002. He then served as chairman before retiring in 2012. ",
  "Under his watch, Wood Group expanded its operations to over 50 countries and now has over 42,000 employees. ",
  "Wood and his family have sold much of their stake in the company over the years, diversifying into other investments."
]